cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.GT, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a model for energy cooperation between cellular base stations, which involves communication and networking aspects. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the control and optimization of energy sharing between base stations with hybrid power supplies. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes an algorithm for online energy cooperation between base stations, which involves distributed computing and communication. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves the optimization of energy sharing between multiple agents (base stations) and can be viewed as a game-theoretic problem. 
5. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) - The paper deals with the emerging technology of renewable energy sources and their integration into cellular networks.
